
== ~/.vim with Rails support

This is my own "~/.vim" directory. It is properly configured to
support Rails development. It features the following.

* colorscheme and basic vimrc setup
* vim rails http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1567
* matchit http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=39
* ruby ftplugin http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=303
* tComment http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1173
* surround http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=1697

== Install
Fork the project to "~/.vim" and create a "~/.vimrc" file
with the following:

  source ~/.vim/vimrc

